1
00:00:24,635 --> 00:00:34,430
~Kimi ga haita shiroi iki ga ima yukkuri kaze ni notte~
<i>*Misty white breaths you exhale, now gently riding on the wind*</i>

2
00:00:34,430 --> 00:00:44,990
~Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku~
<i>*Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away*</i>

3
00:00:44,990 --> 00:00:54,880
~Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo~
<i>*From up above in the sky white clouds reach down*</i>

4
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,291
~Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru~
<i>*To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by*</i>

5
00:00:56,291 --> 00:01:01,548
<i>At the end of the day, when people are rushing home...</i>
~Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru~
<i>*To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by*</i>

6
00:01:01,548 --> 00:01:04,420
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>
~Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru~
<i>*To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by*</i>

7
00:01:04,420 --> 00:01:04,700
~Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru~
<i>*To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by*</i>

8
00:01:06,001 --> 00:01:15,210
~Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne~
<i>*Always seems like a thing of the past*</i>

9
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:20,761
~Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru~
<i>*Clouds passing over a flowing river*</i>

10
00:01:20,761 --> 00:01:26,156
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>
~Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru~
<i>*Clouds passing over a flowing river*</i>

11
00:01:26,398 --> 00:01:31,380
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

12
00:01:34,279 --> 00:01:38,919
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

13
00:01:41,094 --> 00:01:49,212
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
<b>SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3</b>
EP 2: "Tomatoes Wrapped in Pork Belly..."

14
00:01:50,759 --> 00:01:54,259
Master, thank you for everything.

15
00:01:58,549 --> 00:02:00,949
Then, with this...

16
00:02:02,369 --> 00:02:03,829
Ah.

17
00:02:04,729 --> 00:02:08,419
Tezuka-kun, take care of yourself.

18
00:02:24,626 --> 00:02:28,809
He's got the look of someone who is about
to go jump onto the train tracks, huh.

19
00:02:29,709 --> 00:02:31,889
He said he's going back
to the countryside.

20
00:02:32,679 --> 00:02:35,219
Did he fail or something?

21
00:02:35,619 --> 00:02:37,059
Yeah...

22
00:02:40,649 --> 00:02:44,219
Once you fail, it can be quite...

23
00:02:44,809 --> 00:02:48,929
It seems I've gotten used to
seeing people failing.

24
00:02:49,119 --> 00:02:51,329
The sadness of leaving the capital city...

25
00:02:51,329 --> 00:02:53,869
...it's only felt by the people from
the regions, you won't understand.

26
00:02:54,089 --> 00:02:57,019
Didn't you say...
you grew up in Tokyo?

27
00:02:59,869 --> 00:03:01,939
Hello, welcome.

28
00:03:01,939 --> 00:03:04,499
Hello. Tomato Rolls please.

29
00:03:04,499 --> 00:03:05,799
Sure thing.

30
00:03:05,799 --> 00:03:06,959
Come sit...

31
00:03:11,149 --> 00:03:12,459
Nice ambiance, right?

32
00:03:12,459 --> 00:03:14,119
Oh... yes.

33
00:03:14,299 --> 00:03:17,659
Didn't you see him along
the way? Tezuka-kun.

34
00:03:17,849 --> 00:03:19,659
Tezuka?

35
00:03:21,479 --> 00:03:23,069
He came.

36
00:03:23,739 --> 00:03:25,699
Really...

37
00:03:25,699 --> 00:03:28,059
Is he okay?

38
00:03:29,009 --> 00:03:31,069
He ate Tomato Rolls...

39
00:03:31,349 --> 00:03:33,459
...and has gone back to the countryside.

40
00:03:34,189 --> 00:03:37,489
I see, the countryside...

41
00:03:39,549 --> 00:03:44,789
Ah, Master. This guy won the
Newcomer Award... Hashimoto-kun.

42
00:03:44,789 --> 00:03:46,189
Oh, nice to meet you.

43
00:03:46,189 --> 00:03:48,739
Then, congratulations.

44
00:03:49,269 --> 00:03:51,039
- Drink...
- Thank you very much.

45
00:03:51,039 --> 00:03:53,169
Newcomer Award for what?

46
00:03:53,169 --> 00:03:54,159
For manga.

47
00:03:54,159 --> 00:03:56,199
"Big Comic"...

48
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:58,369
I always read that.

49
00:03:58,369 --> 00:04:00,939
His winning story is set
to be published in the next issue.

50
00:04:01,249 --> 00:04:03,299
Right now, there are talks
of having it serialized.

51
00:04:03,299 --> 00:04:06,869
That's amazing, isn't it!
Wait, is it okay...

52
00:04:06,869 --> 00:04:08,929
...if I have his autograph now?

53
00:04:08,929 --> 00:04:10,809
I wonder if it's too early.

54
00:04:28,279 --> 00:04:30,279
I'm digging in.

55
00:04:33,379 --> 00:04:35,519
It's delicious.

56
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:37,179
Told you.

57
00:04:40,669 --> 00:04:43,019
He's called Tezuka Osami.

58
00:04:43,749 --> 00:04:47,649
What a name, huh? It's his real name.

59
00:04:49,189 --> 00:04:52,019
One character away from Tezuka Osamu*?
(*famous mangaka)

60
00:04:52,269 --> 00:04:54,179
Years ago, was he...

61
00:04:54,179 --> 00:04:56,599
Yeah. He was the Newcomer of the Year.

62
00:04:57,269 --> 00:05:00,029
Then, I was put in charge of him.

63
00:05:00,319 --> 00:05:03,799
He wanted to go home though,
because he couldn't live up to his name...

64
00:05:04,899 --> 00:05:07,769
In the end, he didn't become
successful with us...

65
00:05:07,979 --> 00:05:10,769
It seems he was drawing for some
magazine elsewhere but...

66
00:05:12,319 --> 00:05:16,819
I see... he had given up, huh...

67
00:05:18,999 --> 00:05:22,379
Uno-san, I'm gonna do fine.

68
00:05:22,379 --> 00:05:24,989
I have no intention of giving up.

69
00:05:25,699 --> 00:05:29,189
I'm counting on you. 'Cause I was pushing
for you in the preliminary round.

70
00:05:29,189 --> 00:05:32,529
Yes. I already quit
my side job yesterday.

71
00:05:33,209 --> 00:05:35,309
You've burned your bridges, huh!

72
00:05:35,469 --> 00:05:37,949
It's kinda exciting, isn't it!

73
00:05:37,949 --> 00:05:41,479
I'll... cheer for you!

74
00:05:41,769 --> 00:05:43,469
Don't interfere.

75
00:05:43,839 --> 00:05:45,839
Quit bothering em.

76
00:05:52,649 --> 00:05:56,369
<i>It's dangerous to rush inside trains while doors
are closing so please refrain from doing so.</i>
[Big Comic Original, "Hayate Mobius" by
Hashimoto Wataru, Newcomer Awardee!]

77
00:05:56,369 --> 00:05:59,269
- Can I take this?
- Yes, that'll be 320 yen.

78
00:06:02,069 --> 00:06:05,129
This is 1 million, huh...

79
00:06:05,129 --> 00:06:07,589
That's amazing...

80
00:06:07,949 --> 00:06:11,079
Bet you're happy 'cause your
wish has come true.

81
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:14,799
When you turned down those job offers though,
I honestly thought you were a fool.

82
00:06:14,799 --> 00:06:16,529
Yamada, do you wanna read, too?

83
00:06:16,529 --> 00:06:18,119
Sure.

84
00:06:19,169 --> 00:06:22,489
It's 'cause I can't draw anything
except manga.

85
00:06:23,289 --> 00:06:25,319
Wonder if I could aim for it too...

86
00:06:25,319 --> 00:06:27,599
I was told it's impossible so I quit and
became a civil servant.

87
00:06:29,679 --> 00:06:33,589
Ah... I'm gonna be part of
a Japanese delegation.

88
00:06:33,749 --> 00:06:36,889
Of what? Of teachers?

89
00:06:36,889 --> 00:06:38,939
No, soccer.

90
00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:41,209
Aren't you a substitute teacher
in high school?

91
00:07:39,979 --> 00:07:41,999
I'm off.

92
00:07:54,049 --> 00:07:56,529
Ah! Noriko!

93
00:07:58,599 --> 00:08:01,399
Sorry... but my PASMO* has expired.
(*Ticketing card system for trains)

94
00:08:17,539 --> 00:08:21,239
Wakamiya-san, what do you
think about it? Honestly.

95
00:08:21,979 --> 00:08:25,969
I laughed quite a bit.

96
00:08:26,739 --> 00:08:29,019
Laughed...

97
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:35,959
Though there's nothing there
to laugh about.

98
00:08:35,959 --> 00:08:38,439
No, when I said I laughed,
what I meant was...

99
00:08:38,889 --> 00:08:41,429
I wasn't simply laughing.

100
00:08:41,749 --> 00:08:44,229
I was kinda like laughing
around the story.

101
00:08:46,829 --> 00:08:49,619
Uno-san... What did Uno-san say?

102
00:08:49,619 --> 00:08:51,739
Oh... Uno-san's busy.

103
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:54,389
'Cause they're launching
a first issue right now.

104
00:08:54,389 --> 00:08:58,489
No... But his opinion is of a
high level so...

105
00:09:02,819 --> 00:09:06,179
Anyway, the editor-in-chief
isn't convinced.

106
00:09:06,799 --> 00:09:09,259
Whether he wants to let you debut
the series or not.

107
00:09:09,409 --> 00:09:11,539
She doesn't understand it too well.

108
00:09:11,539 --> 00:09:15,679
That Wakamiya-san, to be honest
I don't know what to think of her.

109
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,249
Well for me...

110
00:09:18,249 --> 00:09:21,229
I think she seems a good editor.

111
00:09:21,419 --> 00:09:23,369
No but...

112
00:09:23,369 --> 00:09:26,709
I think it's useless if they're not
committed enough to die in this together...

113
00:09:26,829 --> 00:09:29,129
The mangaka and his editor.

114
00:09:29,129 --> 00:09:32,429
Well it seems, you're
not trying hard enough.

115
00:09:37,129 --> 00:09:41,309
Uno-san, you're committed enough
to die with me, right?

116
00:09:41,309 --> 00:09:43,309
Eh?

117
00:09:45,029 --> 00:09:47,909
I won't lose, no matter what!

118
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:51,209
'Cause I have nothing else but manga.

119
00:10:28,369 --> 00:10:31,879
Sorry... Noriko...

120
00:10:36,459 --> 00:10:39,759
If you have money for drinks,
pay the rent first, will you?

121
00:10:55,259 --> 00:11:01,049
I love manga so much and yet...

122
00:11:26,309 --> 00:11:31,519
This time, I was feeling gloomy...

123
00:11:31,519 --> 00:11:35,419
I pretty much vented out my
feelings directly...

124
00:11:35,419 --> 00:11:37,419
...I mean into the drawings...

125
00:11:54,859 --> 00:11:57,659
Why don't you try reading
these kinds of references?

126
00:11:59,329 --> 00:12:01,829
That person's level is just too low!

127
00:12:04,479 --> 00:12:07,469
Please, just give me
your opinion, too, Uno-san!

128
00:12:08,309 --> 00:12:10,239
Hashimoto-kun...

129
00:12:10,379 --> 00:12:13,279
Do you yourself find this interesting?

130
00:12:13,719 --> 00:12:15,319
Eh?

131
00:12:16,789 --> 00:12:18,799
Do you really think it's interesting?

132
00:12:19,659 --> 00:12:20,709
Yes.

133
00:12:20,709 --> 00:12:23,079
To be honest, it's boring.

134
00:12:23,229 --> 00:12:25,879
No one's gonna pay to read this.

135
00:12:26,799 --> 00:12:29,839
I don't know what Wakamiya
told you but...

136
00:12:30,359 --> 00:12:33,189
You're the one drawing, are you not?

137
00:12:33,289 --> 00:12:36,989
If you lie to yourself,
you'll be disappointed in the end.

138
00:12:48,899 --> 00:12:51,929
Here. This is your last glass.

139
00:12:53,889 --> 00:12:57,069
Haven't heard from him.

140
00:12:57,229 --> 00:12:59,069
I guess he's not drawing.

141
00:13:02,439 --> 00:13:06,319
I'm already accustomed
to disappointments.

142
00:13:07,129 --> 00:13:09,829
Well, it doesn't look like you are.

143
00:13:13,629 --> 00:13:16,649
Even if you turned pro...
those who survive from that point on...

144
00:13:16,649 --> 00:13:19,539
...it'll be a struggle
a dozen times over.

145
00:13:21,039 --> 00:13:24,609
It's true that there will be someone
who'll kill himself...

146
00:13:26,159 --> 00:13:29,099
...just cause he can't draw manga.

147
00:13:36,539 --> 00:13:41,929
The guy who gave up and went back to
the countryside might be happy by now.

148
00:13:41,929 --> 00:13:43,929
You mean Tezuka-kun?

149
00:13:46,779 --> 00:13:50,449
The newcomers I brought here
and ate Tomato Rolls...

150
00:13:50,739 --> 00:13:52,849
...they didn't become successful, huh?

151
00:13:53,889 --> 00:13:57,269
Hey, now. Don't blame my cooking.

152
00:13:58,964 --> 00:14:00,734
I'm joking.

153
00:14:20,669 --> 00:14:22,669
What are you doing?

154
00:14:25,529 --> 00:14:27,319
Hey!

155
00:14:45,269 --> 00:14:47,179
I've had it!!

156
00:14:53,469 --> 00:14:55,529
Why don't you work?

157
00:14:58,659 --> 00:15:02,839
I AM working. Everyday, I'm trying
to come up with a concept...

158
00:15:02,839 --> 00:15:04,429
Do you think I'm stupid?

159
00:15:04,429 --> 00:15:06,729
It hasn't even turned into
a single penny!

160
00:15:09,529 --> 00:15:12,349
It's a work that I have
to build from scratch!

161
00:15:12,529 --> 00:15:14,869
It's not like I a job where I punch in
a time card and get a salary!

162
00:15:14,869 --> 00:15:17,389
You said that you'd quickly
become a mangaka...

163
00:15:17,389 --> 00:15:19,909
...and go pro!

164
00:15:33,319 --> 00:15:35,319
Let's break up already.

165
00:16:18,801 --> 00:16:20,671
Come on!

166
00:16:24,801 --> 00:16:27,701
- Over there, that one.
- Yeah, I get it.

167
00:17:04,111 --> 00:17:06,921
You like... manga?

168
00:17:09,831 --> 00:17:11,831
I also like to draw.

169
00:18:14,041 --> 00:18:16,861
AHH! Shiiit!

170
00:18:44,924 --> 00:18:49,241
I'm already, thinking about
quitting manga.

171
00:18:50,829 --> 00:18:52,789
I see.

172
00:18:53,601 --> 00:18:56,771
It's better if you decide it yourself.

173
00:18:57,941 --> 00:19:00,551
But I'm scared.

174
00:19:00,771 --> 00:19:05,371
If you take manga away from me...
I've got nothing left whatsoever.

175
00:19:05,741 --> 00:19:07,941
I wonder if it's the reverse?

176
00:19:11,346 --> 00:19:14,206
With the intention of
getting rid of everything...

177
00:19:14,562 --> 00:19:17,042
In the end, all that was left...

178
00:19:17,355 --> 00:19:19,605
...was manga, wasn't it?

179
00:19:23,877 --> 00:19:24,981
Welcome.

180
00:19:25,118 --> 00:19:27,408
Master, long time no see.

181
00:19:27,611 --> 00:19:29,971
It's me, Tezuka.

182
00:19:29,971 --> 00:19:32,481
- Tomato Rolls and beer.
- Sure thing.

183
00:19:32,481 --> 00:19:34,641
Oh, she's Yayoi-san.

184
00:19:34,641 --> 00:19:37,161
- Right now, we're drawing together.
- Together?

185
00:19:37,161 --> 00:19:38,651
Yes.

186
00:19:38,651 --> 00:19:40,231
I went back home to the countryside...

187
00:19:40,231 --> 00:19:43,831
I'd been doing caregiver work but...
that's where we met.

188
00:19:43,831 --> 00:19:45,981
Since I was in high school...

189
00:19:45,981 --> 00:19:48,381
...have been drawing
manga as a hobby, too.

190
00:19:48,381 --> 00:19:52,291
I wanted to quickly forget about manga,
that's what I thought but...

191
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:54,811
While I was talking to Yayoi-san,
she also mentioned she wanted to draw...

192
00:19:54,811 --> 00:19:57,011
And so, it seems I became
straightforward with her.

193
00:20:00,338 --> 00:20:04,388
So the two of us kept drawing and
repeatedly sent our works to publishers...

194
00:20:04,388 --> 00:20:06,508
Then, it finally gets to be serialized.

195
00:20:06,508 --> 00:20:09,698
It's great that you've realized
your dream, isn't it?

196
00:20:09,698 --> 00:20:12,328
So today, no matter what,
I wanted Yayoi-san...

197
00:20:12,328 --> 00:20:14,158
...to come and have a taste
of the Tomato Rolls here.

198
00:20:14,158 --> 00:20:18,218
He's always been talking
about your Tomato Rolls.

199
00:20:18,218 --> 00:20:19,868
I'll make it right away.

200
00:20:21,988 --> 00:20:25,688
Are you still gonna use
the name "Tezuka Osami"?

201
00:20:28,598 --> 00:20:32,348
Oh, sorry. Nice to meet you.

202
00:20:32,698 --> 00:20:34,998
I also have been drawing.

203
00:20:34,998 --> 00:20:37,068
Oh... really?

204
00:20:37,688 --> 00:20:41,788
Our names will be together.
I'm no longer bothered about it.

205
00:20:52,568 --> 00:20:54,668
Well? You like it?

206
00:20:54,668 --> 00:20:59,338
Yes! Tomatoes are sweeter when roasted.
It suits the pork.

207
00:20:59,338 --> 00:21:00,978
It's better, right?

208
00:21:00,978 --> 00:21:04,508
Master, here's my payment.

209
00:21:07,638 --> 00:21:10,648
Thank you for everything.

210
00:21:10,988 --> 00:21:12,458
Yeah.

211
00:21:13,278 --> 00:21:16,678
Then, Hashimoto-kun,
take care of yourself.

212
00:21:30,008 --> 00:21:34,458
If you've become tired,
take a break from manga.

213
00:21:38,878 --> 00:21:41,948
When the time comes that
you feel you really want to draw...

214
00:21:41,948 --> 00:21:44,348
Then, you should draw again.

215
00:21:44,998 --> 00:21:47,138
'Cause I did the same thing.

216
00:21:49,618 --> 00:21:51,208
Thank you.

217
00:22:23,258 --> 00:22:25,428
<i>From then on...</i>

218
00:22:25,428 --> 00:22:29,228
<i>...he still hasn't even once
come back to eat Tomato Rolls.</i>

219
00:22:32,968 --> 00:22:35,738
<i>I'll be waiting, Hashimoto-kun.</i>

220
00:22:35,738 --> 00:22:39,178
♫ Skewer and sprinkle with salt

221
00:22:39,178 --> 00:22:42,798
♫ If it turns golden brown

222
00:22:42,798 --> 00:22:48,228
♫ It's delicious when served piping hot

223
00:22:48,848 --> 00:22:51,788
'Master'
KOBAYASHI KAORU

224
00:22:52,348 --> 00:22:55,288
'Hashimoto Wataru'
ISHIDA HOSHI

225
